The region lies between $x = -\sqrt{2}$ and $x = \sqrt{2}$, so the area is $\int_{-\sqrt{2}}^{\sqrt{2}} (5-x^2) - (x^2 + 1) \, dx = \int_{-\sqrt{2}}^{\sqrt{2}} 4 - 2x^2 \, dx = \left[ 4x - \frac{2}{3} x^3 \right]_{-\sqrt{2}}^{\sqrt{2}} = \left( 4\sqrt{2} - \frac{2}{3} (\sqrt{2})^3 \right) - \left( -4\sqrt{2} + \frac{2}{3} (\sqrt{2})^3 \right) = 8 \sqrt{2} - \frac{4}{3} \cdot 2 \sqrt{2} = \boxed{8}$.
